Commands For Moving :
C-a                     : Move to the start of he current line. 
C-e                     : Move to the end of he line. 
C-f                     : Move forward a haracter.  
C-b                     : Move back a character.  
M-f                     : Move forward to the end of the next word.
M-b                     : Move back to the start of this, or the previous, word.
C-l                     : Clear the screen nd redraw the current line.
Commands For Manipulating The History :
C-p                     : Move `up' through the history list. 
C-n                     : Move `down' through the history list. 
C-r                     : Search backward starting at the current line and moving `up' through the history as necessary.
C-d                     : Delete the character under the cursor. If the cursor is at the beginning of the line, there are no characters in the line, and the last character typed was not bound to delete-char, then return EOF.
M-u                     : Uppercase the current (or following) word.
M-l                     : Lowercase the current (or following) word.
M-c                     : A FAIRE :Capitalize the current (or following) word.
Killing And Yanking :
C-k                     : Kill the text from the current cursor position to the end of the line.
M-d                     : Kill from the cursor to the end of the current word, or if between words, to the end of the next word. 
M-DEL                   : Kill the word behind the cursor. 
M-y                     : A FAIRE :Yank the top of the kill ring into the buffer at the current cursor position.
